                            "tier": "intro",
                            "code": "// === ENTRY-LEVEL EXAMPLE ===\n// TASK      - Basic usage of Object Pooling & GC Optimization — understand the core syntax and behavior.\n// APPROACH  - Simple example with minimal parameters; no edge cases.\n// STRENGTHS - Clear, readable; shows the fundamental pattern.\n// WEAKNESSES- Not production-ready; no error handling or complex scenarios.\n// APPROACH  - the simplest object pool: acquire/release particles.\n// STRENGTHS - shows pool pattern with reset, acquire, release.\n// WEAKNESSES- no generic factory, no tracking, no pre-allocation.\n//\n// GOAL: reuse objects to reduce GC pressure\nclass Particle { constructor() { this.reset(); } reset() { this.x = 0; this.y = 0; this.active = false; } }\nconst pool = [];\nfunction acquire() { return pool.pop() || new Particle(); }\nfunction release(p) { p.reset(); pool.push(p); }"
